[4] Russia (Tyumen)
Date: Tue 5 Aug 2014
Source: 4geo.ru/new [in Russian, machine trans., edited]
http://novokuznetsk.4geo.ru/news/show/2014/8/5/kor


The number of cases of measles virus infection continues to grow in the Tyumen Region. To date, 50 cases of the diseases have been confirmed. Of the total number of cases 34 have been children. All the recorded measles cases were individuals who had not been vaccinated against measles. As of 1 Aug 2014, 2 of the patients remain under treatment in an Infectious Diseases Clinic of the hospital. The remainder have been released on recovery. As of 1 Aug 2014, 380 people in contact with measles cases had received immunoglobulin treatment.

Vaccination remains the most appropriate and effective response, protecting the recipients and their contacts. In the Tyumen Region vaccination is provided free of charge.

