[6] New Zealand (Northland)
Date: Tue 5 Aug 2014
Source: New Zealand News [edited]
http://www.newstalkzb.co.nz/auckland/news/nbnat/1386295523-potential-northland-measles-outbreak-minimised


The Northland District Health Board will know by next Tuesday [12 Aug 2014] if the District is experiencing a potential measles outbreak. One Northland child was confirmed to have the disease last week [week of 28 Jul 2014] after coming in contact with infected children from the Waikato.

Northland District Health Board Medical Officer of Health, Dr Clair Mills says public cooperativeness has helped to minimise the spread. She says so far only one other child is showing measles symptoms.

[Byline: Jenee Tibshraeny]

